data.description: Back on the market due to no fault of seller. Priced to sell! Great single family home with detached two car garage and fenced yard. The home needs some TLC however is in overall very good condition and can be moved right into with some cleaning and cosmetic repairs. The "sold as is" home is a three bedroom, two bathroom centrally located house in the desirable Chocolate Drop area of 29 Palms. This is a probate sale with probate approved for sale. It is well appointed with central AC and heat and in addition has a swamp cooler which can be used instead of AC on hot days to save energy costs. It has newer dual pane windows in all rooms and attractive ceramic tile flooring throughout. The home is also all electric. The two car garage is detached. The back yard is fully fenced. The upcoming city of 29 Palms boasts good growth and many new and eclectic businesses in the central downtown area. It is a growing city but still very quaint and has some nice rural areas. The home is close to the downtown shops, restaurants like Kitchen of the Desert and The Ground Squirrel. It is also just a 10 minute or less drive to the Marine base in 29 Palms. It is just a 13 minute drive to Joshua Tree National Parks East entrance. 7 minutes to Luckie Park and the cities events held there. This location is a great jump off to all of the high and low deserts great places to explore and visit. Come make this charming home in the wondrous high desert your pride of ownership.
